WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:50.967
THE APARTMENT JOB

3
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:53.845
Four billion?

4
00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.432
You pocketed four billion won?

5
00:00:58.016 --> 00:01:00.018
Our apartment complex
only has 1.200 households.

6
00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:02.353
and I skimmed that much.

7
00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:03.271
But this place…

8
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:06.983
has almost 10.000 households.

9
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:09.861
Then how much do you think
you can skim off?

10
00:01:10.612 --> 00:01:12.238
A billion? Two billion?

11
00:01:12.322 --> 00:01:14.741
That's pocket change!

12
00:01:15.325 --> 00:01:17.035
You could even skim off ten billion!

13
00:01:20.163 --> 00:01:22.457
I'm serious. Mr. Park!

14
00:01:23.208 --> 00:01:24.125
Ten billion?

15
00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:25.210
Yes.

16
00:01:31.382 --> 00:01:32.425
We can skim off

17
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:33.885
ten billion won

18
00:01:33.968 --> 00:01:35.553
from this apartment complex?

19
00:01:44.395 --> 00:01:45.438
Release him.

20
00:01:45.522 --> 00:01:47.190
What? Oh. okay.

21
00:01:47.273 --> 00:01:48.608
Hey. untie him.

22
00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:05.834
How do we skim off ten billion then?

23
00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:08.586
Well…

24
00:02:10.255 --> 00:02:11.589
you have to become…

25
00:02:13.466 --> 00:02:15.426
the president
of the residents' association.

26
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:18.346
The president?

27
00:02:18.429 --> 00:02:19.722
Me?

28
00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:20.890
Yes.

29
00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:23.101
Tie him up again.

30
00:02:23.184 --> 00:02:25.562
That's enough of your nonsense!

31
00:02:25.645 --> 00:02:27.856
Hey! Don't touch me!

32
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:29.566
The grown-ups are talking.

33
00:02:29.649 --> 00:02:30.942
you little brat.

34
00:02:31.025 --> 00:02:32.861
Didn't you see him giving me my jacket?

35
00:02:33.444 --> 00:02:34.988
Mr. Park.

36
00:02:35.071 --> 00:02:36.990
Just hear me out. okay?

37
00:02:37.073 --> 00:02:39.492
The only people who have access

38
00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:40.535
to the repair reserve fund

39
00:02:40.618 --> 00:02:43.413
are the facility manager
and the president.

40
00:02:43.496 --> 00:02:45.206
If those two are in on it together.

41
00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:48.418
draining an entire apartment complex
would be a piece of cake.

42
00:02:48.501 --> 00:02:51.171
Let's just throw him off.
We have no use for you now.

43
00:02:51.254 --> 00:02:52.589
Wait. stop!

44
00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.508
-Wait! Please!
-Throw him off!

45
00:02:56.801 --> 00:03:00.471
Mr. Park. I saw the notice
in the elevator on my way here.

46
00:03:00.555 --> 00:03:02.307
Your apartment complex

47
00:03:02.390 --> 00:03:05.310
is having
a building representative election.

48
00:03:05.393 --> 00:03:08.730
Become the building representative.
then the president.

49
00:03:08.813 --> 00:03:11.941
Then you'll be able
to pocket ten billion won!

50
00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:14.819
You're telling me to become
a building representative?

51
00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:15.820
Yes.

52
00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:17.989
Hang him.

53
00:03:18.072 --> 00:03:19.490
-Hey. tie him up again.
-All right.

54
00:03:19.574 --> 00:03:21.618
I'm sorry!

55
00:03:21.701 --> 00:03:23.494
I'm so sorry. Mr. Park.

56
00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.204
You're right.

57
00:03:25.788 --> 00:03:29.584
I didn't realize it would be humiliating
for someone like you

58
00:03:29.667 --> 00:03:33.296
to be
an apartment building representative.

59
00:03:33.379 --> 00:03:34.672
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:34.756 --> 00:03:36.215
I'm sorry. Mr. Park.

61
00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:38.927
I'm sorry I hurt your pride.

62
00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:40.428
But there's no other way.

63
00:03:40.511 --> 00:03:42.513
You have to be a building representative…

64
00:03:43.181 --> 00:03:45.767
to qualify to run for president.

65
00:03:46.893 --> 00:03:49.312
Can anyone become the building rep?

66
00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:51.856
Anyone can do it!

67
00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:53.524
Just ask the residents here.

68
00:03:53.608 --> 00:03:55.693
No one even cares about the building rep.

69
00:03:55.777 --> 00:03:56.861
If you volunteer.

70
00:03:56.945 --> 00:03:58.988
you're pretty much guaranteed
to get elected.

71
00:03:59.072 --> 00:04:01.407
I mean it.

72
00:04:01.991 --> 00:04:03.368
I'll get elected…

73
00:04:04.702 --> 00:04:06.162
if I just volunteer?

74
00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:07.538
BUILDING REPRESENTATIVE ELECTION

75
00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:09.457
See? I told you.

76
00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:11.334
You're not seriously buying this. are you?

77
00:04:11.417 --> 00:04:12.418
It's ridiculous.

78
00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:16.798
Boss.

79
00:04:24.681 --> 00:04:26.266
<i>The door is closing.</i>

80
00:05:06.639 --> 00:05:07.640
With ten billion…

81
00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:10.560
we can save Yong-man

82
00:05:10.643 --> 00:05:12.729
and make a fresh start.

83
00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:16.733
But even if you get lucky
and become the representative.

84
00:05:16.816 --> 00:05:19.569
would there really be ten billion here?

85
00:05:20.653 --> 00:05:23.614
If you really don't believe me. call them.

86
00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:24.907
Call who?

87
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.617
The management office.

88
00:05:26.701 --> 00:05:30.163
Ask them how much
the long-term repair reserve fund is.

89
00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:31.539
Long-term what?

90
00:05:31.622 --> 00:05:33.833
What kind of fund is that?

91
00:05:34.709 --> 00:05:35.543
Gosh.

92
00:05:35.626 --> 00:05:38.171
The long-term repair…

93
00:05:38.254 --> 00:05:39.505
You dimwits.

94
00:05:39.589 --> 00:05:43.259
The apartment complex collects money
from residents over a long period.

95
00:05:43.342 --> 00:05:44.510
"Long-term."

96
00:05:44.594 --> 00:05:47.680
If something's broken. you repair it.

97
00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:50.600
"Repair."
Hence. "long-term repair reserve fund."

98
00:05:50.683 --> 00:05:54.604
Please call them
and ask how much they have.

99
00:06:06.991 --> 00:06:08.117
Miss Kang!

100
00:06:09.410 --> 00:06:11.370
What time do you even come to work?

101
00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.498
You're here early. Yun-seo.

102
00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:15.875
I thought I'd be here first today.

103
00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:21.798
It's not even 9:00 yet. Should I answer?

104
00:06:21.881 --> 00:06:23.674
Yes. it could be something urgent.

105
00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:28.596
<i>This is the management office.</i>
<i>How may I help you?</i>

106
00:06:28.679 --> 00:06:31.307
Hello. Good morning.

107
00:06:32.016 --> 00:06:33.017
I'm…

108
00:06:33.601 --> 00:06:35.561
one of the residents.

109
00:06:35.645 --> 00:06:37.230
Well. I…

110
00:06:37.313 --> 00:06:39.690
I wanted to ask you something.

111
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:43.361
The repair reserve fund…

112
00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:49.033
How much is in
the long-term repair reserve fund?

113
00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:53.162
The long-term repair reserve fund?

114
00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:54.288
Well…

115
00:06:54.872 --> 00:06:55.748
Just a moment. sir.

116
00:06:56.290 --> 00:06:58.668
Miss Kang. he's asking
how much is in the repair reserve fund.

117
00:07:00.002 --> 00:07:00.962
Who is it?

118
00:07:01.045 --> 00:07:02.880
A resident. What should I tell him?

119
00:07:05.341 --> 00:07:07.135
Just tell him how much.

120
00:07:08.052 --> 00:07:09.137
Yes. sir.

121
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.722
You want to know how much is in the fund?

122
00:07:11.806 --> 00:07:13.808
Just a moment.

123
00:07:14.976 --> 00:07:18.855
<i>There's 17.857.420.000 won.</i>

124
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.650
<i>Sir. as you probably know.</i>

125
00:07:22.733 --> 00:07:25.445
<i>the apartment complex</i>
<i>will need repairs as it ages.</i>

126
00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:27.530
<i>so we collect fees in advance to save--</i>

127
00:07:29.198 --> 00:07:30.032
Hello?

128
00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:31.868
Sir?

129
00:07:33.911 --> 00:07:35.580
-No way!
-They really have ten billion?

130
00:07:35.663 --> 00:07:37.248
It's more than that. It's 17--

131
00:07:37.331 --> 00:07:39.750
It's 17.857.420.000 won.

132
00:07:39.834 --> 00:07:41.711
Hang on. They actually have it.

133
00:07:41.794 --> 00:07:42.795
I can't believe it.

134
00:07:42.879 --> 00:07:46.591
The facility manager here
must've taken good care of the fund.

135
00:07:46.674 --> 00:07:48.342
It's more than I expected.

136
00:07:49.093 --> 00:07:50.219
Gosh. my knees.

137
00:07:59.729 --> 00:08:01.939
Hey. you're the youngest here. aren't you?

138
00:08:02.023 --> 00:08:04.775
Go and make some hot coffee for me.

139
00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:08.946
So. Mr. Park.

140
00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:10.656
do you believe me now?

141
00:08:11.574 --> 00:08:13.576
Hey. let's actually do this.

142
00:08:13.659 --> 00:08:15.870
That 17.857.420.000 won.

143
00:08:16.454 --> 00:08:19.123
We're going to take it.

144
00:08:22.376 --> 00:08:23.836
THE APARTMENT JOB

145
00:08:27.507 --> 00:08:29.133
Try it like this. Seo-jun.

146
00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:30.051
Yes.

147
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:31.177
Like that.

148
00:08:32.094 --> 00:08:32.970
You did great.

149
00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:34.430
You're doing great.

150
00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:37.141
SAPLING
NAME: MIN-JUN'S TREE

151
00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:38.893
SAPLING
NAME: RU-I

152
00:08:39.852 --> 00:08:41.437
I was so surprised.

153
00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:43.231
How did you come up with this idea?

154
00:08:43.314 --> 00:08:45.191
Now this is real education.

155
00:08:45.274 --> 00:08:46.692
Right?

156
00:08:46.776 --> 00:08:48.444
Donating to an arboretum

157
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:52.573
and using the saplings they gave you
to help teach the children about nature.

158
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:53.950
It's amazing.

159
00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:55.701
You even donate to an arboretum?

160
00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:56.702
You're so thoughtful.

161
00:08:56.786 --> 00:08:58.246
-I know. right?
-I admire that.

162
00:08:58.329 --> 00:09:00.581
I thought that planting saplings
with the kids

163
00:09:00.665 --> 00:09:02.750
would be good
for their emotional development.

164
00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:05.336
It's nothing special.

165
00:09:05.419 --> 00:09:07.213
You're so cool.

166
00:09:08.339 --> 00:09:09.507
What is this?

167
00:09:10.091 --> 00:09:13.844
Who said you could
plant stuff like this here?

168
00:09:15.596 --> 00:09:16.973
This is ridiculous.

169
00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:21.435
Don't you know how expensive
our apartment complex is?

170
00:09:21.519 --> 00:09:24.814
They poured a fortune
into the landscaping design.

171
00:09:24.897 --> 00:09:27.275
Who gave you permission
to plant this crap here?

172
00:09:27.358 --> 00:09:28.192
What?

173
00:09:28.776 --> 00:09:31.320
What did you say? "Crap"?

174
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.072
How can you say such a thing?

175
00:09:33.155 --> 00:09:34.657
Did I say anything wrong?

176
00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:38.369
Whose land is this? Is it yours?

177
00:09:38.452 --> 00:09:39.328
Excuse me.

178
00:09:39.412 --> 00:09:42.039
We can plant stuff here
if we're residents.

179
00:09:42.123 --> 00:09:43.416
I'm a resident too.

180
00:09:43.499 --> 00:09:45.876
There are loads of residents here.

181
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.212
You should get their permission.

182
00:09:48.296 --> 00:09:50.298
It's not like we did something bad.

183
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:51.591
It's for the kids' education.

184
00:09:51.674 --> 00:09:52.883
Mothers.

185
00:09:52.967 --> 00:09:54.844
let me tell you something. Listen up.

186
00:09:54.927 --> 00:09:57.221
I get your enthusiasm.
but this tacky parenting.

187
00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:58.973
-Goodness.
-Tacky?

188
00:09:59.056 --> 00:10:00.850
Just do it in your own homes!

189
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:04.895
We're teaching them about nature

190
00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.856
and how to respect life.

191
00:10:06.939 --> 00:10:08.316
You call that tacky?

192
00:10:08.399 --> 00:10:09.984
You actually have a point.

193
00:10:10.067 --> 00:10:12.278
Fine. but before you teach them that.

194
00:10:12.361 --> 00:10:14.405
why don't you teach them

195
00:10:14.488 --> 00:10:18.576
about shared communities
and respecting your neighbors first?

196
00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:20.494
"Nature"? You've got to be kidding me.

197
00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:24.457
Then should I try planting lettuce.
peppers. and cabbage

198
00:10:24.540 --> 00:10:25.791
all over the place?

199
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:26.876
That's different.

200
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:29.670
What's different? It's the same!

201
00:10:29.754 --> 00:10:31.547
Hurry up and pull these out!

202
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:32.506
What if we won't?

203
00:10:33.215 --> 00:10:34.675
-You won't?
-No.

204
00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:35.593
No!

205
00:10:39.263 --> 00:10:40.723
All right. then.

206
00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:44.435
Hey!

207
00:10:46.312 --> 00:10:47.688
I can't believe this!

208
00:10:48.564 --> 00:10:49.565
What's she doing?

209
00:10:49.649 --> 00:10:50.816
She must be crazy!

210
00:10:50.900 --> 00:10:52.652
-What are you doing?
-Stop it!

211
00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:54.862
She really pisses me off.

212
00:10:54.945 --> 00:10:56.238
I can't believe her.

213
00:10:56.322 --> 00:10:57.406
She's so stuck up.

214
00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.867
Did you hear her going on about rules?

215
00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:01.744
She was so annoying.

216
00:11:01.827 --> 00:11:03.496
Who even is she?

217
00:11:03.579 --> 00:11:05.081
It's obvious. isn't it?

218
00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:07.667
She's just an ignorant person.

219
00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:09.293
Actually.

220
00:11:09.377 --> 00:11:11.629
I overheard the guards talking about her.

221
00:11:11.712 --> 00:11:13.464
They said she's a former beauty queen.

222
00:11:13.547 --> 00:11:15.841
No way. Miss Korea?

223
00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:17.385
A beauty queen? That's insane.

224
00:11:17.468 --> 00:11:20.054
I bet she won a lunatic contest.
not a beauty pageant.

225
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:22.723
That's crazy.

226
00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:24.809
I'm not sure about the details.

227
00:11:24.892 --> 00:11:29.271
but I heard that there are photos of her
from the beauty pageant

228
00:11:29.355 --> 00:11:31.148
plastered all over her walls.

229
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:33.984
They must be fake photos.
That can't be true.

230
00:11:34.068 --> 00:11:35.861
In any case.

231
00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:36.946
I think we need someone

232
00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:40.199
to represent us young mothers
in our apartment complex.

233
00:11:41.075 --> 00:11:43.911
There are over 3000 preschoolers here.

234
00:11:43.994 --> 00:11:46.914
but there's no one
to speak for all those mothers.

235
00:11:46.997 --> 00:11:49.375
You have a great point.

236
00:11:49.458 --> 00:11:52.002
Someone who can understand us
and take our side

237
00:11:52.086 --> 00:11:54.505
should be president
of the residents' association

238
00:11:54.588 --> 00:11:55.673
for us to have influence.

239
00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:58.134
-You're right.
-They're electing the building reps.

240
00:11:58.217 --> 00:12:00.678
Won't they pick the president
from among them?

241
00:12:00.761 --> 00:12:02.221
-Yes.
-I think so.

242
00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:04.640
You know.

243
00:12:04.723 --> 00:12:06.308
you should try running.

244
00:12:07.143 --> 00:12:08.436
We'll give you our full support.

245
00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:11.397
Me?

246
00:12:11.981 --> 00:12:14.358
You're thoughtful and socially conscious.

247
00:12:14.442 --> 00:12:16.277
You should be a voice for us mothers.

248
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:19.071
If you run this time.
we'll back you up no matter what.

249
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:21.240
Yes. you can do it.

250
00:12:22.324 --> 00:12:23.576
How would I…

251
00:12:26.495 --> 00:12:28.956
But who's the current president?

252
00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:33.294
I don't know.

253
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:35.629
I have no idea.

254
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:39.884
Yes?

255
00:12:39.967 --> 00:12:41.177
PRESIDENT SEO GANG-WON

256
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:49.310
Is everything all right?

257
00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:53.105
I…

258
00:12:57.318 --> 00:12:58.235
Sir.

259
00:12:58.319 --> 00:13:01.030
"I…"

260
00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:04.283
Whenever you hesitate like that.

261
00:13:04.366 --> 00:13:06.911
it turns out to be something troublesome.

262
00:13:06.994 --> 00:13:08.037
You're scaring me.

263
00:13:09.288 --> 00:13:10.289
Well.

264
00:13:10.372 --> 00:13:12.291
some young mothers caused a scene

265
00:13:12.374 --> 00:13:15.503
over planting saplings in a flower bed
within the complex.

266
00:13:16.086 --> 00:13:17.379
Is that so?

267
00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:20.799
I wrapped up the issue by saying
we'd discuss it during a meeting. but--

268
00:13:20.883 --> 00:13:25.346
I told you several times
that it'll die down if we stay quiet.

269
00:13:25.429 --> 00:13:28.599
Don't cause a bigger problem
by getting involved.

270
00:13:28.682 --> 00:13:30.017
and just leave it be.

271
00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:31.852
Don't do anything.

272
00:13:31.936 --> 00:13:34.897
The trick to staying on
as a facility manager for years

273
00:13:34.980 --> 00:13:38.484
is to just laugh it off and do nothing…

274
00:13:39.401 --> 00:13:41.529
no matter what the residents say.

275
00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:43.614
Right.

276
00:13:47.201 --> 00:13:50.663
Is there another "I…" to say to me?

277
00:13:50.746 --> 00:13:52.248
Why aren't you leaving?

278
00:13:53.666 --> 00:13:57.836
Ha-jeong is saying
she'll stop doing that job.

279
00:14:09.723 --> 00:14:13.018
An acquaintance of mine
gave this tea to me.

280
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:16.480
The scent is quite nice.

281
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:22.111
I heard your sister became a lawyer.

282
00:14:22.194 --> 00:14:23.070
Congratulations.

283
00:14:23.153 --> 00:14:25.364
She must be quite amazing.

284
00:14:26.240 --> 00:14:27.491
Thank you.

285
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:32.288
You heard from Mr. Choi. right?

286
00:14:33.622 --> 00:14:34.748
I can't do…

287
00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:36.667
that job anymore.

288
00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:39.378
But…

289
00:14:39.461 --> 00:14:41.547
if your sister finds out

290
00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:46.093
what kind of money
you've been supporting her studies with.

291
00:14:46.176 --> 00:14:48.304
wouldn't she be
pretty disappointed in you?

292
00:14:48.387 --> 00:14:50.848
I just think that your sister

293
00:14:50.931 --> 00:14:54.351
would be better off not knowing
about what you've been doing.

294
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:59.690
But I really can't do it any longer.

295
00:15:00.774 --> 00:15:02.359
I won't tell anyone about it.

296
00:15:02.943 --> 00:15:04.737
I promise to keep my mouth shut.

297
00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:09.825
If you feel uneasy with me here.

298
00:15:09.909 --> 00:15:12.661
I'll resign from the management office.

299
00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.038
Just let me quit.

300
00:15:17.374 --> 00:15:18.500
Did you think that

301
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:22.588
if you said you'd back out
on your own like this.

302
00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:24.757
I'd just say. "Sure. do as you please"?

303
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:28.052
Do you really think
I'd just let you leave?

304
00:15:34.391 --> 00:15:36.518
I'm just kidding.

305
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:40.898
It was a joke.

306
00:15:40.981 --> 00:15:43.275
This tastes nice. Go on.

307
00:15:47.363 --> 00:15:49.698
"A facility manager
in an apartment complex

308
00:15:49.782 --> 00:15:51.992
with 1200 households has been suspected

309
00:15:52.076 --> 00:15:55.204
of embezzling four billion won
over five years by falsifying accounts.

310
00:15:55.287 --> 00:15:58.666
The police are currently tracking
his whereabouts." So what?

311
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:02.503
That guy the article's talking about

312
00:16:02.586 --> 00:16:03.879
is me.

313
00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:06.382
Wow. you're a total scumbag.

314
00:16:06.465 --> 00:16:07.716
Hang on.

315
00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:10.135
The complex residents
aren't doing anything

316
00:16:10.219 --> 00:16:12.012
even after losing all that money?

317
00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:14.014
Well. technically speaking.

318
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:17.142
it's the same as each household
losing about 30.000 won a month.

319
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:21.063
Who would waste their time and energy
to get that tiny sum back?

320
00:16:21.146 --> 00:16:23.107
No one in Korea would do that.

321
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.192
Everyone's busy with their own lives.

322
00:16:25.275 --> 00:16:28.237
It's better for them to just work
and earn money in that time.

323
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.531
They don't even care about it.

324
00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.620
That's why we can skim off the money?

325
00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:38.330
Because they don't care?

326
00:16:40.457 --> 00:16:43.544
WHAT IS THE LONG-TERM REPAIR RESERVE FUND?

327
00:16:45.879 --> 00:16:48.257
Before we begin. raise your hand

328
00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:51.593
if you've ever lived
in an apartment complex before.

329
00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:54.471
Put them down.

330
00:16:54.555 --> 00:16:56.390
Then while you were living there.

331
00:16:56.473 --> 00:17:01.270
has anyone ever been curious about
what the long-term repair reserve fund is?

332
00:17:02.896 --> 00:17:04.773
Right? I understand.

333
00:17:04.857 --> 00:17:08.777
Loads of people have no idea what this is.
even if they live in an apartment.

334
00:17:08.861 --> 00:17:10.279
Just start explaining.

335
00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:12.781
To put it simply…

336
00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:16.785
it's a fund collected in advance
for long-term repairs

337
00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.871
for the apartment complex.

338
00:17:18.954 --> 00:17:20.330
If residents are asked to pay

339
00:17:20.414 --> 00:17:22.583
for the fees all at once later.
they'll be pissed.

340
00:17:22.666 --> 00:17:24.835
As people get older.

341
00:17:24.918 --> 00:17:27.254
their bodies start hurting here and there.

342
00:17:27.337 --> 00:17:29.506
It's the same for apartment buildings.

343
00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:32.551
So this fund is saved for such moments!

344
00:17:32.634 --> 00:17:37.014
That's what
the long-term repair reserve fund is.

345
00:17:37.097 --> 00:17:40.100
Mr. Park. how much did you pay
into the fund this month?

346
00:17:41.852 --> 00:17:43.270
29.360 won.

347
00:17:43.353 --> 00:17:46.482
Let's round it down to 29.000 won.

348
00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:48.067
And how many households?

349
00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:49.401
There are 9800 households.

350
00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:51.862
9.800 households.

351
00:17:51.945 --> 00:17:53.739
-Multiply it and--
-It's 284.2 million.

352
00:17:56.366 --> 00:17:57.826
Right.

353
00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:00.913
That amount has been piling up each month.

354
00:18:00.996 --> 00:18:04.500
and now. there's about 17.85 billion won

355
00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:05.918
sitting in that fund!

356
00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:08.420
So the people managing the fund

357
00:18:08.504 --> 00:18:10.631
are the president and facility manager?

358
00:18:10.714 --> 00:18:11.965
That's it.

359
00:18:12.549 --> 00:18:14.384
Then I'll beat those two up

360
00:18:14.468 --> 00:18:17.012
and join our old boss Yong-man.

361
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:18.097
Sit down.

362
00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:21.934
Just take care of your health.

363
00:18:22.976 --> 00:18:26.939
Your apartment complex is electing
building representatives right now.

364
00:18:27.022 --> 00:18:30.776
and if you become one.
you qualify to run for president.

365
00:18:31.693 --> 00:18:34.238
Doesn't this seem like fate. Mr. Park?

366
00:18:35.322 --> 00:18:37.282
You pocketed four billion
over five years. right?

367
00:18:37.366 --> 00:18:39.535
-Yes.
-But we don't have that much time.

368
00:18:39.618 --> 00:18:40.828
We only have three months.

369
00:18:40.911 --> 00:18:43.038
Don't worry about that.

370
00:18:43.122 --> 00:18:46.250
If you become the president.
you'll get the official seal.

371
00:18:46.333 --> 00:18:48.836
To execute payments. you need
the president's and the manager's seal.

372
00:18:48.919 --> 00:18:52.923
With those. you can just stamp it.
withdraw the cash and flee abroad.

373
00:18:53.006 --> 00:18:53.882
That's it.

374
00:18:54.550 --> 00:18:56.385
So we'd just need the manager's seal.

375
00:18:56.468 --> 00:18:57.719
That's what I'm telling you.

376
00:18:57.803 --> 00:19:00.097
Then how would we acquire that?

377
00:19:00.180 --> 00:19:01.098
Come on!

378
00:19:01.181 --> 00:19:02.891
You guys are big and strong.

379
00:19:02.975 --> 00:19:05.102
It'll be easy to get your hands
on one seal.

380
00:19:05.185 --> 00:19:07.521
You can hang him off the rooftop
like you did to me

381
00:19:07.604 --> 00:19:09.398
or coax him into splitting it with you.

382
00:19:09.481 --> 00:19:11.441
You can decide on that later.

383
00:19:11.525 --> 00:19:13.360
But first. Mr. Park.

384
00:19:13.443 --> 00:19:15.112
you have to run for building rep.

385
00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:19.575
The 17.857.420.000 won

386
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:23.203
along with the money we have
would be 21.357.420.000 won.

387
00:19:25.038 --> 00:19:25.956
That would be enough…

388
00:19:26.582 --> 00:19:27.875
to protect Yong-man

389
00:19:27.958 --> 00:19:31.753
and help Gyeong-nam. Je-gil.
and Big Guy achieve their dreams.

390
00:19:32.421 --> 00:19:34.339
I have to pull this off.

391
00:19:34.423 --> 00:19:35.507
no matter what.

392
00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:38.844
SEOUL JUNGBU DETENTION CENTER

393
00:19:41.471 --> 00:19:44.683
Hey. why are you visiting so often?

394
00:19:44.766 --> 00:19:47.019
Why do you look so awful? Let me see.

395
00:19:47.644 --> 00:19:49.646
Are there guys bullying you in there?

396
00:19:49.730 --> 00:19:51.773
Of course not.

397
00:19:51.857 --> 00:19:53.734
They treat me with respect

398
00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:57.654
since I was the former boss
of the Oasis Gang.

399
00:19:57.738 --> 00:20:01.241
They let me use the bathroom first
in the morning

400
00:20:01.325 --> 00:20:03.327
and give me the most meat
during our meals.

401
00:20:03.410 --> 00:20:05.996
Should I keep going?

402
00:20:10.375 --> 00:20:11.877
I just feel sorry. that's all.

403
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:13.879
Just hang in there.

404
00:20:13.962 --> 00:20:15.839
I found a way to get you out.

405
00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:19.676
Don't do anything bad
because of me. Hae-kang.

406
00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.470
It's nothing bad.

407
00:20:21.553 --> 00:20:23.347
Then what is it?

408
00:20:26.099 --> 00:20:27.935
Nobody's getting harmed.

409
00:20:28.018 --> 00:20:29.353
so it's nothing bad.

410
00:20:29.436 --> 00:20:30.771
Park Hae-kang.

411
00:20:30.854 --> 00:20:32.314
You told me to focus on my life.

412
00:20:35.108 --> 00:20:37.402
I need you in my life.

413
00:20:37.486 --> 00:20:39.029
I need you. so…

414
00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:41.823
just get ready to leave.

415
00:21:00.634 --> 00:21:02.219
DAILY REPAYMENT. SAME-DAY LOAN

416
00:21:07.432 --> 00:21:09.768
5-MINUTE LOAN
NO COLLATERAL OR GUARANTOR REQUIRED

417
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:11.061
Hey. Hae-kang.

418
00:21:11.144 --> 00:21:12.813
-Go on in.
-Hurry.

419
00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:20.279
I heard you took
Dongseong Temple's donation box.

420
00:21:20.362 --> 00:21:23.699
The head monk owes over 50 million won.

421
00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:28.662
Why would you do something
I didn't even tell you to do?

422
00:21:29.997 --> 00:21:31.498
You'll hurt yourself. you idiot.

423
00:21:33.959 --> 00:21:35.168
Take it easy. okay?

424
00:21:36.336 --> 00:21:37.212
Yes. Boss.

425
00:21:47.556 --> 00:21:49.182
LOAN AGREEMENT

426
00:22:02.863 --> 00:22:04.489
I heard your father died.

427
00:22:06.783 --> 00:22:12.456
I've been keeping this
in case he asked for you again…

428
00:22:13.415 --> 00:22:15.083
but I don't need it now.

429
00:22:23.675 --> 00:22:24.760
You can leave.

430
00:22:25.677 --> 00:22:27.095
Don't do anything dangerous…

431
00:22:27.846 --> 00:22:29.639
and just do what you want.

432
00:22:31.558 --> 00:22:34.770
It's the end for us now.

433
00:22:48.283 --> 00:22:49.284
I…

434
00:22:49.367 --> 00:22:51.036
I want to stay here.

435
00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:54.164
With you. Boss.

436
00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:17.104
What's going on?

437
00:23:17.854 --> 00:23:19.481
I don't know. Was there an accident?

438
00:23:19.564 --> 00:23:21.024
Why aren't you moving your car? Hey!

439
00:23:21.108 --> 00:23:23.693
-Just a moment.
-Hurry up!

440
00:23:23.777 --> 00:23:25.028
Of course. Please wait.

441
00:23:25.112 --> 00:23:28.156
Sir. why don't we talk
after you move your car first?

442
00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:30.033
-Don't you see this?
-No.

443
00:23:30.117 --> 00:23:31.118
Why should I?

444
00:23:31.201 --> 00:23:33.370
Sir. you're causing inconvenience
for the residents

445
00:23:33.453 --> 00:23:34.621
by blocking the parking lot.

446
00:23:34.704 --> 00:23:35.914
What about me?

447
00:23:36.498 --> 00:23:37.666
What about my inconvenience?

448
00:23:37.749 --> 00:23:39.543
I'm a resident here too!

449
00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:41.878
So why the hell did you stick

450
00:23:41.962 --> 00:23:44.881
-this parking violation notice on my car?
-Record this.

451
00:23:44.965 --> 00:23:46.633
Do you know how much this car costs?

452
00:23:46.716 --> 00:23:51.388
Sir. that was because you kept parking
across two or three spaces…

453
00:23:51.471 --> 00:23:53.807
-Yun-seo…
-Right?

454
00:23:54.307 --> 00:23:58.103
We kept getting complaints.
so we had no choice.

455
00:23:58.186 --> 00:24:01.690
I live here. I pay the maintenance fees
and park where I want.

456
00:24:01.773 --> 00:24:04.901
What does it matter to you
if I take two or three spaces?

457
00:24:04.985 --> 00:24:07.904
I'm replacing my windshield.
so bring me ten million for that.

458
00:24:07.988 --> 00:24:09.281
Sir!

459
00:24:09.364 --> 00:24:12.576
You've been parking terribly
over and over again!

460
00:24:12.659 --> 00:24:15.287
If you don't move your car.
we're reporting this.

461
00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:16.830
-I'm calling the cops!
-The cops?

462
00:24:16.913 --> 00:24:18.373
-What are you doing?
-Calm down.

463
00:24:18.456 --> 00:24:20.917
Lady. you think calling the cops
will change anything?

464
00:24:21.001 --> 00:24:22.377
This isn't a public road.

465
00:24:22.460 --> 00:24:24.880
so the police can't tow my car.

466
00:24:24.963 --> 00:24:26.840
Don't act so bold if you're ignorant!

467
00:24:26.923 --> 00:24:28.758
How dare you call me ignorant?

468
00:24:28.842 --> 00:24:30.051
You're the one who's ignorant!

469
00:24:34.973 --> 00:24:37.100
Move!

470
00:24:47.194 --> 00:24:49.446
Oh. my gosh. Are they crazy?

471
00:24:49.529 --> 00:24:50.822
Nice. How satisfying.

472
00:24:57.746 --> 00:25:00.540
Wait… Wait!

473
00:25:01.249 --> 00:25:02.250
What?

474
00:25:02.918 --> 00:25:04.044
What's wrong with you?

475
00:25:04.127 --> 00:25:05.337
Have you lost your mind?

476
00:25:05.420 --> 00:25:06.546
How…

477
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:12.636
How can you just ram into
someone else's car like this?

478
00:25:12.719 --> 00:25:15.347
You seemed to be unable to move your car.
so I did it for you.

479
00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:17.015
Don't be ridiculous.

480
00:25:17.098 --> 00:25:19.017
Do you know how much this costs?

481
00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:20.936
It's 300 million won!

482
00:25:21.019 --> 00:25:23.063
-Were you prepared for that?
-It's 300 million.

483
00:25:23.146 --> 00:25:25.941
He's going to have to pay
300 million for his temper.

484
00:25:26.024 --> 00:25:28.193
I have no money to give
to someone like you.

485
00:25:28.777 --> 00:25:30.904
You can sue me or report me.
Whatever you like.

486
00:25:30.987 --> 00:25:33.573
Would the police even do anything?

487
00:25:33.657 --> 00:25:35.492
Okay. fine.

488
00:25:36.284 --> 00:25:39.079
Nobody's entering the parking lot today!

489
00:25:41.873 --> 00:25:44.125
Don't do this. Come on.

490
00:25:54.177 --> 00:25:55.220
CHUNG-WON

491
00:25:55.303 --> 00:25:56.304
All right.

492
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:02.143
I'm sorry.

493
00:26:02.227 --> 00:26:05.480
I scratched your car.
so I'll compensate you for it.

494
00:26:05.563 --> 00:26:09.025
Why is this apartment complex
filled with psychos?

495
00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:12.654
This car is really expensive.
Are you loaded?

496
00:26:15.073 --> 00:26:17.325
It looks like a budget model
from about ten years ago.

497
00:26:17.409 --> 00:26:21.121
Looking at its condition. it seems like
you got it used for about 80 million.

498
00:26:21.204 --> 00:26:23.957
Of course. I'll compensate you for it.

499
00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:27.043
The thing about a car

500
00:26:27.127 --> 00:26:29.879
is that once it's been repaired.
it depreciates massively.

501
00:26:29.963 --> 00:26:31.673
I'll cover everything.

502
00:26:31.756 --> 00:26:33.049
Mr. Kim.

503
00:26:33.133 --> 00:26:36.845
compensate him in full
so he won't feel upset.

504
00:26:36.928 --> 00:26:38.013
Yes. sir.

505
00:26:38.513 --> 00:26:40.181
But I'm a businessman.

506
00:26:40.265 --> 00:26:43.560
so I only feel satisfied
when calculations are precise.

507
00:26:43.643 --> 00:26:46.604
You wasted my precious evening

508
00:26:46.688 --> 00:26:49.232
and the time of all the residents here.

509
00:26:49.316 --> 00:26:50.817
caused a disturbance.

510
00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:54.529
and interfered
with the management office's work.

511
00:26:54.612 --> 00:26:57.157
so I'm planning on suing you for that.

512
00:26:57.240 --> 00:26:58.074
What do you say?

513
00:26:58.658 --> 00:27:01.119
I have about 12 lawyers in my company.

514
00:27:01.202 --> 00:27:02.912
Do you think you can handle that?

515
00:27:06.082 --> 00:27:07.292
I'm going to sue you too.

516
00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:08.752
You should.

517
00:27:08.835 --> 00:27:11.212
Our lawyers are excellent at their job.

518
00:27:11.296 --> 00:27:12.964
They're good at digging up dirt.

519
00:27:13.048 --> 00:27:14.174
picking people apart.

520
00:27:14.257 --> 00:27:17.427
and completely destroying their lives.

521
00:27:17.510 --> 00:27:18.803
That's their specialty.

522
00:27:18.887 --> 00:27:22.182
All within legal boundaries. of course.

523
00:27:24.225 --> 00:27:26.811
So can you move your car now?

524
00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:33.777
-Where is he going?
-Is he running away?

525
00:27:34.861 --> 00:27:37.530
He's the guy living in the penthouse
in Building 123. isn't he?

526
00:27:37.614 --> 00:27:39.991
He's so cool.

527
00:27:40.075 --> 00:27:41.701
Isn't he so cool?

528
00:27:42.535 --> 00:27:44.287
He really is cool.

529
00:27:44.371 --> 00:27:46.915
I was the one
who damaged the car in the end.

530
00:27:46.998 --> 00:27:48.917
so my secretary
will take care of everything.

531
00:27:49.417 --> 00:27:51.378
We'll handle the repair costs
for your car too.

532
00:27:51.461 --> 00:27:52.462
That's all right.

533
00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:54.214
I'll handle my own car.

534
00:27:54.297 --> 00:27:57.092
You dealt with the troublesome nuisance

535
00:27:57.175 --> 00:27:59.427
and helped save my time.

536
00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:02.180
It's only fair that
I handle your repair costs as well.

537
00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:07.477
I'm Lee Chung-won from Building 123.

538
00:28:14.150 --> 00:28:16.111
I'm Park Hae-kang from Building 114.

539
00:28:19.864 --> 00:28:22.075
You're really cool. sir!

540
00:28:22.158 --> 00:28:23.910
Everyone. applause!

541
00:28:23.993 --> 00:28:24.994
You're so cool!

542
00:28:25.745 --> 00:28:26.830
You're amazing!

543
00:28:28.456 --> 00:28:29.541
He's so cool.

544
00:28:31.793 --> 00:28:34.546
I ended up having to kiss him!

545
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:37.549
What? You did what?

546
00:28:37.632 --> 00:28:38.550
We…

547
00:28:40.176 --> 00:28:41.094
We kissed.

548
00:28:42.137 --> 00:28:43.346
For real?

549
00:28:43.430 --> 00:28:46.891
Still. if it weren't for him.
you would've been short on money.

550
00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:48.518
But what about this month?

551
00:28:50.270 --> 00:28:51.396
I don't know.

552
00:28:51.479 --> 00:28:52.564
Here. take this.

553
00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:54.774
Seriously?

554
00:28:54.858 --> 00:28:57.026
You're delivering milk to earn that money?

555
00:28:57.110 --> 00:28:58.403
You look so exhausted.

556
00:29:01.656 --> 00:29:02.741
It's 3000 won.

557
00:29:03.491 --> 00:29:04.492
What's 3000 won?

558
00:29:04.576 --> 00:29:06.411
That probiotic drink you're drinking.

559
00:29:09.956 --> 00:29:13.168
I have to buy it? Fine. I will.

560
00:29:13.251 --> 00:29:15.587
And I'll pay for dinner as well.

561
00:29:15.670 --> 00:29:17.213
Forget dinner.

562
00:29:17.297 --> 00:29:19.382
Can't you just buy all of these
while you're at it?

563
00:29:22.135 --> 00:29:24.012
No. this is crazy.

564
00:29:24.095 --> 00:29:26.431
Just go and talk to your sister.

565
00:29:26.514 --> 00:29:29.225
Tell her the truth
and just ask her for help one more time.

566
00:29:30.059 --> 00:29:31.144
This is insane.

567
00:29:31.227 --> 00:29:33.313
I know. but.

568
00:29:33.396 --> 00:29:36.191
I can't bear to see
the disappointment on her face.

569
00:29:36.274 --> 00:29:39.277
And how can I do that to her
when she helped me for ten years?

570
00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:41.404
She should focus on her own life now.

571
00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:48.119
<i>Then.</i>

572
00:29:48.203 --> 00:29:50.580
how about this?

573
00:29:50.663 --> 00:29:53.208
Just do this until the end of my term.

574
00:29:53.291 --> 00:29:54.501
That's fine. isn't it?

575
00:30:08.973 --> 00:30:09.808
Hey. Ha-jeong.

576
00:30:11.059 --> 00:30:12.560
Were you waiting for me?

577
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:26.074
I treated my colleagues to dinner today

578
00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:27.951
to celebrate my sister becoming a lawyer.

579
00:30:28.910 --> 00:30:30.411
Why would you treat them?

580
00:30:31.371 --> 00:30:33.456
Hey. I've been working there
for six years.

581
00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:35.750
but I never treated them to anything.

582
00:30:36.334 --> 00:30:39.587
And I never joined them for dinner
unless it was a company gathering.

583
00:30:39.671 --> 00:30:42.131
You know I'm not a morning person.

584
00:30:42.215 --> 00:30:44.175
But I woke up early

585
00:30:44.259 --> 00:30:47.804
every day for six years
to pack lunch so I could save money.

586
00:30:47.887 --> 00:30:49.013
Six years.

587
00:30:50.265 --> 00:30:52.475
I know.

588
00:30:53.434 --> 00:30:55.728
I'm not that smart.

589
00:30:55.812 --> 00:30:58.690
but I've been working really hard
to support you.

590
00:30:59.566 --> 00:31:00.900
I know that.

591
00:31:01.401 --> 00:31:03.695
But why are you saying this?

592
00:31:03.778 --> 00:31:05.864
You're starting to scare me.

593
00:31:08.324 --> 00:31:09.367
Ha-ri.

594
00:31:12.161 --> 00:31:14.873
Can it be my turn now?

595
00:31:14.956 --> 00:31:16.749
It's time for you to help me.

596
00:31:17.917 --> 00:31:20.962
You know my dream was to be a patissier.

597
00:31:21.588 --> 00:31:23.590
I want to try that again.

598
00:31:24.924 --> 00:31:26.968
Before it's too late

599
00:31:27.051 --> 00:31:29.137
and before I get any worse.

600
00:31:29.220 --> 00:31:31.055
I want a new start.

601
00:31:31.681 --> 00:31:32.891
What do you mean. "worse"?

602
00:31:33.641 --> 00:31:36.686
You're not treating people badly
like you do to me. are you?

603
00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:38.396
Of course not.

604
00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:40.732
Just forget that.

605
00:31:42.191 --> 00:31:43.651
But you'll help me. won't you?

606
00:31:44.652 --> 00:31:45.486
<i>This is it.</i>

607
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.697
<i>If I miss this chance.</i>
<i>I'll never be able to tell her.</i>

608
00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:48.990
<i>I should tell her the truth.</i>

609
00:31:50.742 --> 00:31:51.618
Kang Ha-jeong.

610
00:31:53.912 --> 00:31:56.331
Live your own life now.
I'll help you as much as I can.

611
00:31:57.248 --> 00:31:58.166
You mean it?

612
00:31:58.958 --> 00:32:01.377
Really? Hang on.

613
00:32:01.461 --> 00:32:04.839
I should enroll in classes
and buy an oven and stuff.

614
00:32:04.923 --> 00:32:06.758
Thank you. Ha-ri!

615
00:32:07.926 --> 00:32:08.760
Goodness.

616
00:32:09.594 --> 00:32:11.012
I can't believe it.

617
00:32:14.641 --> 00:32:15.767
I'm screwed.

618
00:32:25.693 --> 00:32:26.527
What are you doing?

619
00:32:26.611 --> 00:32:28.655
I'm sorry. sir.

620
00:32:28.738 --> 00:32:31.074
but you'll have to get to work
a bit late today.

621
00:32:31.157 --> 00:32:32.742
I'll get a company car here right away.

622
00:32:32.825 --> 00:32:33.910
Why?

623
00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:40.541
It seems like someone played a prank.

624
00:32:40.625 --> 00:32:41.709
A prank?

625
00:32:53.346 --> 00:32:56.516
Let's check the dashcam.

626
00:33:06.734 --> 00:33:07.610
<i>You…</i>

627
00:33:14.200 --> 00:33:16.411
I'm feeling a bit stiff today.

628
00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:19.664
Mr. Kim…

629
00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:22.583
how about a round of morning golf?

630
00:33:22.667 --> 00:33:24.002
Yes. sir.

631
00:33:24.085 --> 00:33:25.169
I'll make the preparations.

632
00:33:29.173 --> 00:33:30.883
{\an8}UNDER REPAIR
WILL BE COMPLETED SOON

633
00:33:47.984 --> 00:33:50.236
I'm not hitting the ball well today.

634
00:33:50.319 --> 00:33:53.531
I need to hit the sweet spot
to get that satisfying feel.

635
00:33:55.408 --> 00:33:57.160
License plate number 9007.

636
00:33:57.994 --> 00:34:00.747
Let me tell you something
that you should keep in mind.

637
00:34:00.830 --> 00:34:03.207
Wait. is it a lease. or does he own it?

638
00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:05.251
He rents.

639
00:34:07.670 --> 00:34:09.630
You rent?

640
00:34:09.714 --> 00:34:11.591
Then you'll understand even better.

641
00:34:11.674 --> 00:34:14.469
You're renting. so that apartment unit
belongs to someone else.

642
00:34:14.552 --> 00:34:16.137
The real owner.

643
00:34:18.681 --> 00:34:20.391
Listen carefully.

644
00:34:27.774 --> 00:34:29.692
In our apartment complex.

645
00:34:29.776 --> 00:34:32.653
there are a bunch of idiots
who think this place is theirs

646
00:34:32.737 --> 00:34:36.365
just because their name is written
on the documents.

647
00:34:37.158 --> 00:34:38.993
But this apartment complex…

648
00:34:39.577 --> 00:34:40.411
is mine…

649
00:34:41.954 --> 00:34:45.124
and anyone who messes with
what's mine on my own turf…

650
00:34:48.461 --> 00:34:50.254
is dead meat.

651
00:34:56.844 --> 00:34:57.845
It's all right.

652
00:34:59.013 --> 00:35:02.225
And if you drop this. you're dead.

653
00:35:05.603 --> 00:35:07.730
Sir!

654
00:35:11.776 --> 00:35:13.027
All right…

655
00:35:13.986 --> 00:35:15.947
I'm swinging for real this time.

656
00:35:16.030 --> 00:35:18.491
No! Sir!

657
00:35:29.293 --> 00:35:31.212
Those young mothers.

658
00:35:31.295 --> 00:35:33.881
they're so disrespectful.

659
00:35:34.549 --> 00:35:37.135
And that car owner
has zero parking etiquette.

660
00:35:37.218 --> 00:35:40.471
Can I really just sit back
and ignore this kind of chaos

661
00:35:40.555 --> 00:35:44.100
in my apartment complex. my camellia?

662
00:35:45.268 --> 00:35:49.105
Should I just become the building rep
and set this place straight?

663
00:35:52.066 --> 00:35:57.113
My dear residents of True Value State…

664
00:35:57.822 --> 00:35:59.907
if I become the building representative.

665
00:35:59.991 --> 00:36:01.909
I will take care of all the disorder

666
00:36:01.993 --> 00:36:04.203
in this apartment complex

667
00:36:04.287 --> 00:36:08.207
and make this a place where common sense

668
00:36:08.291 --> 00:36:10.084
prevails!

669
00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:11.002
{\an8}Thank you!

670
00:36:11.085 --> 00:36:12.170
{\an8}CANDIDATE REGISTRATION FORM

671
00:36:13.838 --> 00:36:16.549
That's it.

672
00:36:16.632 --> 00:36:17.466
Right?

673
00:36:20.011 --> 00:36:21.262
You're home.

674
00:36:21.345 --> 00:36:22.221
Yeah.

675
00:36:25.224 --> 00:36:26.684
Hey.

676
00:36:27.185 --> 00:36:28.060
What?

677
00:36:28.144 --> 00:36:29.937
How many times do I have to tell you

678
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:32.982
not to wear that jacket?

679
00:36:34.483 --> 00:36:35.610
It's our university jacket.

680
00:36:36.194 --> 00:36:37.820
Are you proud of that?

681
00:36:38.321 --> 00:36:40.531
Are you proud of attending
a university like that?

682
00:36:40.615 --> 00:36:43.326
How can you not be ashamed at all?

683
00:36:43.409 --> 00:36:45.745
I'm going to run
for building representative.

684
00:36:45.828 --> 00:36:49.498
You should think about my position too.

685
00:36:49.582 --> 00:36:53.252
"You should think about my position too."
What are you even saying?

686
00:36:53.336 --> 00:36:54.629
Hey!

687
00:36:54.712 --> 00:36:57.256
Stop wearing that jacket. okay?

688
00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.591
I feel so dizzy.

689
00:36:58.674 --> 00:37:00.051
CANDIDATE REGISTRATION FORM

690
00:37:00.760 --> 00:37:04.263
You've been staring at that application
for hours.

691
00:37:04.347 --> 00:37:05.765
I told you. no one cares.

692
00:37:06.349 --> 00:37:09.101
You can just make up half of it.

693
00:37:09.185 --> 00:37:10.937
-Geez.
-He's right. sir.

694
00:37:11.020 --> 00:37:13.272
This isn't a real election anyway.

695
00:37:13.356 --> 00:37:16.692
How about saying
you graduated from Stanford University?

696
00:37:16.776 --> 00:37:18.069
Stamp? What university is that?

697
00:37:18.152 --> 00:37:19.737
It's the one I want my son to attend.

698
00:37:19.820 --> 00:37:21.155
Let's say he led a soccer club.

699
00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:23.282
an alumni association.
and a merchants' association.

700
00:37:23.366 --> 00:37:24.700
Wait.

701
00:37:24.784 --> 00:37:26.744
That's a violation of election law.

702
00:37:26.827 --> 00:37:29.997
I didn't expect that of him.
but he's really uptight.

703
00:37:30.748 --> 00:37:33.042
I think we should show more sincerity.

704
00:37:33.125 --> 00:37:34.418
I have to be honest.

705
00:37:34.502 --> 00:37:36.879
Write that I only have a GED.

706
00:37:36.963 --> 00:37:40.633
-Wait. that's…
-Okay. then for your experience…

707
00:37:40.716 --> 00:37:42.885
"Former Strategic Planning Team member
of Oasis Group.

708
00:37:42.969 --> 00:37:45.388
and current CEO of HK Trading
and Investment." Nice. right?

709
00:37:45.471 --> 00:37:46.931
But sir. there's no sincerity.

710
00:37:47.014 --> 00:37:49.267
Really? Then how about this?

711
00:37:49.350 --> 00:37:52.311
"Served as operations chief
and enforcer for the Oasis Gang.

712
00:37:52.395 --> 00:37:53.771
then became the boss.

713
00:37:53.854 --> 00:37:55.856
Currently retired." How about that?

714
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:58.276
If I reveal the fact that I was in a gang.

715
00:37:58.359 --> 00:38:00.027
it'll only scare the residents.

716
00:38:00.111 --> 00:38:01.070
You're right.

717
00:38:01.779 --> 00:38:02.613
Let's go…

718
00:38:03.489 --> 00:38:05.533
with a self-made entrepreneur vibe.

719
00:38:06.534 --> 00:38:08.411
Perfect. We're almost there.

720
00:38:08.494 --> 00:38:10.246
What about your campaign promises?

721
00:38:11.122 --> 00:38:12.790
Say I'll improve this apartment complex.

722
00:38:12.873 --> 00:38:14.166
Improve it how?

723
00:38:15.501 --> 00:38:18.087
I'll make this
a very good apartment complex.

724
00:38:25.052 --> 00:38:27.763
Oh. my arm. Goodness.

725
00:38:29.432 --> 00:38:30.725
Just write it down.

726
00:38:30.808 --> 00:38:32.560
-What do I write?
-What he just said.

727
00:38:35.396 --> 00:38:37.356
The photo studio's ready. sir.

728
00:38:45.406 --> 00:38:47.450
All right. let's begin.

729
00:38:47.950 --> 00:38:49.160
One. two. three.

730
00:38:49.785 --> 00:38:50.703
Lower it a bit.

731
00:38:50.786 --> 00:38:51.662
Here we go.

732
00:38:53.164 --> 00:38:54.874
All right. That's good.

733
00:38:54.957 --> 00:38:57.418
-Great.
-Looking good. sir.

734
00:38:57.960 --> 00:39:01.297
-You really suit a building rep.
-They're so excited.

735
00:39:06.344 --> 00:39:07.219
MANAGEMENT OFFICE

736
00:39:20.107 --> 00:39:21.108
<i>Three months.</i>

737
00:39:21.776 --> 00:39:26.614
<i>I'll become the president.</i>
<i>take the fund and flee in three months.</i>

738
00:39:31.577 --> 00:39:33.371
Hello. May I help you?

739
00:39:33.454 --> 00:39:34.497
Hello.

740
00:39:34.997 --> 00:39:36.665
Do I apply for building rep here?

741
00:39:36.749 --> 00:39:37.625
Yes.

742
00:39:41.295 --> 00:39:42.129
Okay.

743
00:39:44.965 --> 00:39:47.426
You're from Building 114.

744
00:39:48.594 --> 00:39:49.887
DISTRICT 6
CHA YUN-JO

745
00:39:49.970 --> 00:39:51.013
DISTRICT 4
SHIN BONG-SU

746
00:39:54.558 --> 00:39:55.434
Do you live alone?

747
00:39:56.018 --> 00:39:56.852
Why?

748
00:39:57.353 --> 00:39:58.813
Is there a problem with that?

749
00:39:58.896 --> 00:40:00.231
It's not that.

750
00:40:00.314 --> 00:40:03.734
People running for building representative
are usually heads of households

751
00:40:03.818 --> 00:40:06.278
or members of three-generation households.

752
00:40:07.113 --> 00:40:09.031
I've never seen anyone living alone

753
00:40:09.115 --> 00:40:11.200
run for building representative.

754
00:40:12.410 --> 00:40:15.037
You must be quite invested
in your living conditions.

755
00:40:15.996 --> 00:40:18.499
But it doesn't mean
you can't register as a candidate.

756
00:40:19.875 --> 00:40:22.002
I'll come back later. I forgot something.

757
00:40:34.473 --> 00:40:35.641
Let's go.

758
00:40:36.267 --> 00:40:39.854
My daughter-in-law sent me some cash
because she got a raise.

759
00:40:39.937 --> 00:40:41.021
I'll treat you to coffee.

760
00:40:41.105 --> 00:40:44.108
-Congratulations.
-Don't be silly.

761
00:40:44.942 --> 00:40:45.776
Wait up!

762
00:40:54.910 --> 00:40:58.164
I've never seen anyone living alone
run for building representative.

763
00:40:59.290 --> 00:41:00.332
<i>I only just realized…</i>

764
00:41:02.042 --> 00:41:06.422
<i>that an apartment complex is</i>
<i>a community of families living together.</i>

765
00:41:12.428 --> 00:41:13.262
Salute!

766
00:41:13.345 --> 00:41:15.723
<i>I overlooked the fact that</i>
<i>communities like this</i>

767
00:41:15.806 --> 00:41:17.475
<i>don't tolerate anything unusual.</i>

768
00:41:22.146 --> 00:41:25.941
<i>At this rate. I'm going to fail for sure.</i>

769
00:41:30.321 --> 00:41:31.822
Oh. my stomach. Hey. you're back.

770
00:41:31.906 --> 00:41:32.740
My stomach.

771
00:41:33.699 --> 00:41:35.534
What? What are you doing?

772
00:41:35.618 --> 00:41:37.828
It seems like
you were just stalling for time.

773
00:41:37.912 --> 00:41:39.163
but that won't work on me.

774
00:41:39.663 --> 00:41:41.415
What's with you? Let me go.

775
00:41:41.999 --> 00:41:43.459
What's going on. sir?

776
00:41:43.542 --> 00:41:46.629
Have you ever seen
a single man becoming the president?

777
00:41:48.547 --> 00:41:50.382
Have you?

778
00:41:51.467 --> 00:41:52.301
No. I haven't.

779
00:41:52.384 --> 00:41:55.179
You fraud. I knew it.
Should we hang him off the roof again?

780
00:41:55.262 --> 00:41:57.223
Lots of people live alone these days.

781
00:41:57.306 --> 00:41:58.599
so I thought it'd be fine.

782
00:41:58.682 --> 00:42:00.935
Wait. Mr. Park.
I really need to use the bathroom.

783
00:42:05.272 --> 00:42:07.107
Thanks. Hang on.

784
00:42:14.406 --> 00:42:15.241
A family.

785
00:42:16.575 --> 00:42:19.203
We need a family
to take that repair reserve fund.

786
00:42:19.286 --> 00:42:20.120
A family?

787
00:42:20.913 --> 00:42:22.289
Yes. an ordinary family.

788
00:42:22.373 --> 00:42:24.667
Mom. Dad. Grandma. Grandpa.
People like that.

789
00:42:24.750 --> 00:42:27.878
Most households are families
in this apartment complex.

790
00:42:28.712 --> 00:42:30.714
No one will vote for some strange man

791
00:42:30.798 --> 00:42:34.301
living alone with three other men.

792
00:42:35.469 --> 00:42:37.513
Where could we acquire a family?

793
00:42:38.722 --> 00:42:39.557
I'll get it.

794
00:42:43.227 --> 00:42:44.144
A family.

795
00:42:45.854 --> 00:42:48.774
I think the hotel wedding team sent this.

796
00:42:48.857 --> 00:42:51.110
They said they'd frame
the wedding photo and send it.

797
00:42:51.193 --> 00:42:52.111
This must be it.

798
00:42:55.698 --> 00:42:56.991
The photo came out great.

799
00:42:57.074 --> 00:42:58.742
Should we hang it in the living room?

800
00:42:58.826 --> 00:43:01.787
Hey. why would we hang this
in the living room?

801
00:43:01.870 --> 00:43:03.497
It's not like he really got married.

802
00:43:03.581 --> 00:43:05.082
Take that to the balcony.

803
00:43:05.165 --> 00:43:06.959
They really look like a couple. though.

804
00:43:07.042 --> 00:43:08.586
-They look like newlyweds.
-Look.

805
00:43:10.838 --> 00:43:11.880
The photo's nice.

806
00:43:13.007 --> 00:43:14.633
You look so handsome.

807
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:18.804
We're going to…

808
00:43:19.513 --> 00:43:21.515
recruit this woman as my wife.

809
00:43:26.645 --> 00:43:27.605
Is this the place?

810
00:43:28.188 --> 00:43:30.316
Yes. the stand-in service owner

811
00:43:30.399 --> 00:43:33.360
refused to give me her number
because of privacy laws.

812
00:43:33.444 --> 00:43:35.195
so I had to pay them for it.

813
00:43:35.279 --> 00:43:38.866
When I tracked her location.
it came up as a law firm in this building.

814
00:43:39.908 --> 00:43:42.828
As someone working in law.
let me tell you something.

815
00:43:42.911 --> 00:43:45.706
Stay on the right side of the law.

816
00:43:47.166 --> 00:43:48.584
So she's a lawyer?

817
00:43:49.084 --> 00:43:51.045
What if she really is a lawyer?

818
00:43:51.629 --> 00:43:53.505
She has a decent job with good pay.

819
00:43:53.589 --> 00:43:55.466
She'd have no reason to be your fake wife.

820
00:43:57.384 --> 00:43:59.094
Then why did she do the bride gig?

821
00:44:04.683 --> 00:44:05.934
Five million won.

822
00:44:06.018 --> 00:44:07.144
Deal.

823
00:44:07.770 --> 00:44:08.604
Money.

824
00:44:08.687 --> 00:44:10.564
She'll be persuaded with money.

825
00:44:12.191 --> 00:44:13.817
-Let's go.
-Okay.

826
00:44:21.867 --> 00:44:22.993
-Thank you.
-No problem.

827
00:44:24.620 --> 00:44:26.664
There's no lawyer named Kang Ha-ri.

828
00:44:27.247 --> 00:44:28.874
I'm sure it's this place.

829
00:44:35.964 --> 00:44:37.257
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATION

830
00:44:40.594 --> 00:44:43.097
{\an8}WEE PARTNERS
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATION APPLICATION

831
00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:54.316
I just…

832
00:44:55.234 --> 00:44:57.361
touched it
because I thought it was my own leg.

833
00:45:00.239 --> 00:45:01.281
You must be surprised too.

834
00:45:01.865 --> 00:45:04.535
But that's the truth.

835
00:45:04.618 --> 00:45:05.452
I got confused.

836
00:45:06.703 --> 00:45:08.831
You were confused about your own leg?

837
00:45:08.914 --> 00:45:11.125
It was an accident.

838
00:45:11.208 --> 00:45:14.336
I just touched her leg by accident.
That's not sexual harassment.

839
00:45:14.920 --> 00:45:16.547
I just got played by a gold digger.

840
00:45:17.297 --> 00:45:18.465
But you know.

841
00:45:18.549 --> 00:45:21.552
it was all filmed on a security camera.

842
00:45:22.302 --> 00:45:23.178
Here.

843
00:45:24.430 --> 00:45:26.515
{\an8}The woman next to you was dozing off.

844
00:45:26.598 --> 00:45:28.851
{\an8}and you were groping her thigh.

845
00:45:29.435 --> 00:45:30.811
There's no way out of this.

846
00:45:31.645 --> 00:45:32.896
You should just admit it.

847
00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:34.982
apologize and reach a settlement.

848
00:45:35.065 --> 00:45:36.108
Are you blind?

849
00:45:37.359 --> 00:45:39.403
What makes you think I was groping her?

850
00:45:39.903 --> 00:45:41.488
Settlement? Are you kidding me?

851
00:45:42.531 --> 00:45:44.074
I'm suing her for false accusations.

852
00:45:44.783 --> 00:45:45.742
Sir.

853
00:45:45.826 --> 00:45:48.620
the law isn't something
you can take lightly.

854
00:45:49.872 --> 00:45:52.166
Are you taking her side
because you're a woman too?

855
00:45:52.749 --> 00:45:53.584
Sir.

856
00:45:53.667 --> 00:45:55.878
I'm not taking sides or trying to argue.

857
00:45:55.961 --> 00:45:57.963
-As you can see in the footage--
-Miss.

858
00:45:59.381 --> 00:46:02.593
Honestly. if she was exposing
her bare legs like that in public.

859
00:46:02.676 --> 00:46:04.386
isn't she partly responsible?

860
00:46:04.470 --> 00:46:06.138
She was asking for it.

861
00:46:07.639 --> 00:46:10.601
So it's not fair
to call that sexual harassment!

862
00:46:11.351 --> 00:46:13.395
Not fair? You disgusting pervert!

863
00:46:13.479 --> 00:46:14.730
What? "Disgusting pervert"?

864
00:46:16.315 --> 00:46:19.776
Some countries flog sex offenders
before imprisoning them.

865
00:46:19.860 --> 00:46:21.236
Do you know what flogging is?

866
00:46:21.320 --> 00:46:22.654
It's when someone is beaten

867
00:46:22.738 --> 00:46:25.324
with full force for showing disrespect
toward the law and women.

868
00:46:25.407 --> 00:46:26.992
Guys like you should be beaten up.

869
00:46:27.075 --> 00:46:28.952
you filthy piece of trash!

870
00:46:29.036 --> 00:46:29.912
Trash?

871
00:46:30.954 --> 00:46:33.749
Do you have a death wish? How dare you?

872
00:46:33.832 --> 00:46:35.209
Let me give you a slap.

873
00:46:35.292 --> 00:46:36.793
You need to learn a lesson.

874
00:46:38.212 --> 00:46:39.213
Who's this jerk?

875
00:46:42.799 --> 00:46:45.135
I have urgent business
with this woman here.

876
00:46:45.219 --> 00:46:46.553
So will you excuse us?

877
00:46:48.931 --> 00:46:50.516
One. two…

878
00:46:53.477 --> 00:46:55.229
How did you--

879
00:46:55.312 --> 00:46:56.522
Let's talk for a moment.

880
00:46:57.397 --> 00:47:00.817
Sir. please use the next counter
for your consultation.

881
00:47:01.818 --> 00:47:03.362
Miss Kang. we need to talk. Right now.

882
00:47:04.112 --> 00:47:04.988
Follow me.

883
00:47:11.870 --> 00:47:14.498
Do I have to put up with an asshole
if he's a customer?

884
00:47:14.581 --> 00:47:16.583
Watch your language.

885
00:47:16.667 --> 00:47:19.044
I have human rights too. you know.

886
00:47:19.753 --> 00:47:21.463
Right. sure.

887
00:47:22.005 --> 00:47:23.465
But before that…

888
00:47:24.841 --> 00:47:26.510
let's discuss your performance.

889
00:47:27.803 --> 00:47:30.097
None of your consultations
have led to actual cases.

890
00:47:30.806 --> 00:47:34.518
The consultations I handled
didn't really require formal cases. so I--

891
00:47:34.601 --> 00:47:36.186
Are you a lawyer?

892
00:47:37.813 --> 00:47:39.648
Well. no. but…

893
00:47:40.274 --> 00:47:41.858
Didn't you say the free consultations

894
00:47:41.942 --> 00:47:44.069
are part of Wee Partners'
social contribution efforts?

895
00:47:44.152 --> 00:47:46.780
Even social contribution programs
come with expenses.

896
00:47:48.282 --> 00:47:50.242
Miss Kang. you are terminated as of today.

897
00:47:50.325 --> 00:47:51.201
What?

898
00:47:51.285 --> 00:47:52.578
Clear out your desk.

899
00:47:52.661 --> 00:47:54.746
Article 23 of the Labor Standards Act

900
00:47:54.830 --> 00:47:58.584
states that an employer shall not dismiss.
suspend. transfer or otherwise discipline

901
00:47:58.667 --> 00:48:00.586
a worker without just cause.

902
00:48:01.169 --> 00:48:03.755
Did you forget that
you're working at a law firm?

903
00:48:03.839 --> 00:48:07.259
Everyone here knows
the Labor Standards Act.

904
00:48:07.342 --> 00:48:09.803
If you feel this is unfair.
you can report it.

905
00:48:11.013 --> 00:48:11.847
I…

906
00:48:33.827 --> 00:48:35.871
I just got fired.

907
00:48:35.954 --> 00:48:36.913
What do I do?

908
00:48:37.956 --> 00:48:39.541
Do you have some money?

909
00:48:39.625 --> 00:48:42.628
Can't you dip into your savings
for the sake of our friendship?

910
00:48:44.921 --> 00:48:46.465
No. I didn't mean it.

911
00:48:47.049 --> 00:48:49.343
I told my sister to do what she wanted.

912
00:48:49.426 --> 00:48:50.552
I'm screwed.

913
00:48:53.180 --> 00:48:54.765
I was waiting for you. Miss Kang Ha-ri.

914
00:49:02.481 --> 00:49:03.940
How did you know my name?

915
00:49:04.024 --> 00:49:05.359
And my workplace?

916
00:49:05.442 --> 00:49:08.737
I had to meet you. so I asked around.

917
00:49:10.572 --> 00:49:13.283
Did you know that leaking personal data
may be punishable

918
00:49:13.367 --> 00:49:17.245
by up to 5 years in prison
or a fine of up to 50 million won?

919
00:49:17.329 --> 00:49:19.289
And if you've obtained
personal information

920
00:49:19.373 --> 00:49:21.041
through improper means

921
00:49:21.124 --> 00:49:24.211
or used information
learned in the course of your duties

922
00:49:24.294 --> 00:49:27.047
for other purposes.
you may be subject to up to three years…

923
00:49:27.756 --> 00:49:28.715
Keep going.

924
00:49:30.717 --> 00:49:31.718
Never mind.

925
00:49:32.719 --> 00:49:33.762
What did you want to say?

926
00:49:34.346 --> 00:49:35.681
Let's work on something together.

927
00:49:36.807 --> 00:49:37.849
Why would I do that?

928
00:49:38.767 --> 00:49:41.103
Play the role of my wife for three months.

929
00:49:42.187 --> 00:49:43.980
Play the role of what?

930
00:49:44.064 --> 00:49:45.315
My wife.

931
00:49:45.399 --> 00:49:48.193
Just think of it
as another stand-in service gig.

932
00:49:48.276 --> 00:49:49.236
No.

933
00:49:49.820 --> 00:49:51.238
Aren't you in need of money?

934
00:49:51.321 --> 00:49:52.989
I'm always in need of money.

935
00:49:53.073 --> 00:49:54.908
Well. I need you and you need money.

936
00:49:54.991 --> 00:49:56.243
It'll be a win-win situation.

937
00:49:56.326 --> 00:49:57.703
I don't need your money.

938
00:49:57.786 --> 00:49:58.787
Why not?

939
00:49:58.870 --> 00:50:00.831
Because it's dirty money?

940
00:50:01.623 --> 00:50:03.709
I don't know why you need a wife.

941
00:50:03.792 --> 00:50:06.336
but I'm sure it's shady work
with shady money.

942
00:50:07.212 --> 00:50:08.088
Let me ask one thing.

943
00:50:10.298 --> 00:50:11.967
Are you in a gang?

944
00:50:12.551 --> 00:50:15.679
It's pretty big. right?
I saw all those guys at the wedding.

945
00:50:16.763 --> 00:50:18.098
Let me be clear.

946
00:50:18.181 --> 00:50:19.558
I've retired.

947
00:50:19.641 --> 00:50:22.519
but even after we retire.
we attend important events for each other.

948
00:50:24.479 --> 00:50:26.773
-So you're not in a gang anymore.
-What?

949
00:50:26.857 --> 00:50:28.066
Still. my answer is no.

950
00:50:28.150 --> 00:50:30.986
As someone working in law.
I don't want to get involved with you.

951
00:50:32.487 --> 00:50:34.740
I believe you're no longer working in law.

952
00:50:37.576 --> 00:50:41.037
I'll excuse myself first.
I hope we don't meet each other again.

953
00:50:41.121 --> 00:50:44.166
Do you care about background
even when it comes to money?

954
00:50:44.249 --> 00:50:46.334
Money doesn't have
a good or bad education.

955
00:50:46.418 --> 00:50:48.837
or differences
in social status or occupation.

956
00:50:48.920 --> 00:50:51.673
Money is just money. Why would you refuse?

957
00:50:56.928 --> 00:50:58.054
A hundred million.

958
00:50:59.806 --> 00:51:01.391
A hundred million for three months.

959
00:51:03.685 --> 00:51:06.271
I'll give you 30 million
as a down payment right away.

960
00:51:08.356 --> 00:51:09.566
<i>Did he say 30 million?</i>

961
00:51:09.649 --> 00:51:11.818
<i>With that. I could help Ha-jeong</i>

962
00:51:11.902 --> 00:51:14.154
<i>and not have to worry about money</i>
<i>for a while.</i>

963
00:51:14.237 --> 00:51:16.907
<i>Are you mad?</i>
<i>What the hell are you thinking?</i>

964
00:51:16.990 --> 00:51:18.408
<i>You want to accept his money?</i>

965
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:20.619
<i>Get a grip!</i>

966
00:51:26.792 --> 00:51:27.793
Deal.

967
00:51:27.876 --> 00:51:29.085
I CAN DO IT!

968
00:51:29.169 --> 00:51:30.462
Whatever.

969
00:51:34.049 --> 00:51:35.801
{\an8}KANG HA-RI'S BANK ACCOUNT
30.098.607 WON

970
00:51:36.843 --> 00:51:38.261
It's only three months.

971
00:51:39.012 --> 00:51:41.723
Just think of it
as a long-term stand-in service gig.

972
00:51:41.807 --> 00:51:42.974
You can do it. Kang Ha-ri!

973
00:51:43.058 --> 00:51:44.059
Let's do this!

974
00:51:47.813 --> 00:51:50.607
Sir. did she really…

975
00:51:51.316 --> 00:51:53.151
say "deal" and agree to it?

976
00:51:53.235 --> 00:51:54.861
She'll do anything for money.

977
00:51:55.612 --> 00:51:56.738
It makes things easier.

978
00:51:56.822 --> 00:51:58.865
So we got a wife.

979
00:51:59.449 --> 00:52:01.618
You're keeping an eye
on the Lizard. right?

980
00:52:02.869 --> 00:52:03.703
Yes.

981
00:52:07.666 --> 00:52:09.501
I was just doing some fortune reading.

982
00:52:09.584 --> 00:52:10.544
I'll stop.

983
00:52:13.088 --> 00:52:14.714
I'll clean this up. It's messy.

984
00:52:15.966 --> 00:52:17.217
My socks.

985
00:52:19.427 --> 00:52:21.346
What is it? Say something.

986
00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:23.473
Just tell me.

987
00:52:23.557 --> 00:52:25.225
Be my father.

988
00:52:26.768 --> 00:52:28.103
If you play the role of my father

989
00:52:28.186 --> 00:52:30.480
and cooperate
until I become the president.

990
00:52:30.564 --> 00:52:33.275
I'll clear all your debt.

991
00:52:34.234 --> 00:52:35.819
You're a wanted man.

992
00:52:35.902 --> 00:52:37.612
so you have nowhere to go anyway.

993
00:52:39.364 --> 00:52:40.198
Deal.

994
00:52:43.785 --> 00:52:44.619
Wait.

995
00:52:46.204 --> 00:52:48.790
Do I get a bonus if we succeed?

996
00:52:50.292 --> 00:52:51.585
I'll let you live.

997
00:53:04.139 --> 00:53:06.850
I knew it was my lucky day today.

998
00:53:08.518 --> 00:53:10.020
Of course I miss you.

999
00:53:10.812 --> 00:53:13.565
So did you brush your teeth or not?

1000
00:53:13.648 --> 00:53:14.649
Let me see.

1001
00:53:16.109 --> 00:53:19.154
Make sure to brush your teeth well.
or you'll get cavities.

1002
00:53:21.114 --> 00:53:22.741
Hey. Gyeong-buk. It's Uncle Hae-kang.

1003
00:53:22.824 --> 00:53:24.284
<i>Uncle!</i>

1004
00:53:24.367 --> 00:53:27.329
You've gotten
even more handsome. Gyeong-buk.

1005
00:53:27.412 --> 00:53:29.039
You should greet him properly.

1006
00:53:29.956 --> 00:53:32.125
I have to get back to work now.

1007
00:53:32.208 --> 00:53:34.085
so listen to your grandma and go to bed.

1008
00:53:34.169 --> 00:53:35.670
<i>Goodnight. Dad.</i>

1009
00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:40.383
Gyeong-buk's grown so much.

1010
00:53:41.593 --> 00:53:43.219
He seems to grow every day.

1011
00:53:43.303 --> 00:53:44.721
You must miss him.

1012
00:53:50.310 --> 00:53:52.062
Well. I have no other choice.

1013
00:53:52.145 --> 00:53:53.438
Let's bring him here.

1014
00:53:53.521 --> 00:53:54.606
What?

1015
00:53:54.689 --> 00:53:58.193
Let's raise him as my son
until our project's over.

1016
00:54:00.904 --> 00:54:04.157
You said you wanted him
to attend Stanford University.

1017
00:54:04.240 --> 00:54:05.450
Then he should learn English.

1018
00:54:06.034 --> 00:54:08.286
How long will you keep him
stuck in the countryside?

1019
00:54:08.370 --> 00:54:09.955
He can't learn any English there.

1020
00:54:10.622 --> 00:54:12.248
This is a good opportunity for him.

1021
00:54:12.332 --> 00:54:13.500
Let's send him…

1022
00:54:14.292 --> 00:54:15.460
to an English kindergarten.

1023
00:54:15.543 --> 00:54:17.587
An English kindergarten?

1024
00:54:25.720 --> 00:54:27.514
<i>The preparations are complete.</i>

1025
00:54:28.098 --> 00:54:30.308
<i>It's time to begin.</i>

1026
00:54:36.606 --> 00:54:39.025
FAMILY PHOTO SHOOT
MODEL APPLICATIONS

1027
00:54:48.284 --> 00:54:49.119
Sir…

1028
00:54:49.953 --> 00:54:51.037
I brought coffee.

1029
00:54:51.121 --> 00:54:52.747
-Big Guy.
-Right.

1030
00:54:55.333 --> 00:54:56.751
Are you an artist or what?

1031
00:54:57.252 --> 00:54:59.504
Don't be so rude.

1032
00:55:00.338 --> 00:55:02.674
I'm going for a retired artist vibe.

1033
00:55:03.591 --> 00:55:04.592
Don't I look cool?

1034
00:55:04.676 --> 00:55:08.722
I was popular among the ladies
when I was young.

1035
00:55:09.264 --> 00:55:11.224
I'll win over the elderly women

1036
00:55:11.307 --> 00:55:15.228
and help you secure the election.

1037
00:55:19.691 --> 00:55:21.609
Superman!

1038
00:55:21.693 --> 00:55:22.819
Uncle!

1039
00:55:22.902 --> 00:55:24.362
Gyeong-buk!

1040
00:55:25.947 --> 00:55:27.741
When did you get so big. kiddo?

1041
00:55:28.366 --> 00:55:29.284
Uncle.

1042
00:55:29.367 --> 00:55:31.870
I missed you so much.

1043
00:55:32.412 --> 00:55:34.330
I missed you too. kiddo.

1044
00:55:37.625 --> 00:55:39.836
He didn't even give his own dad a kiss.

1045
00:55:39.919 --> 00:55:40.879
I feel upset.

1046
00:55:40.962 --> 00:55:43.089
He was always so nice to Gyeong-buk.

1047
00:55:43.173 --> 00:55:44.049
Gyeong-buk!

1048
00:55:44.632 --> 00:55:45.592
Let me carry…

1049
00:55:45.675 --> 00:55:47.260
I can't now. You carry him.

1050
00:55:47.343 --> 00:55:48.303
You're so cute.

1051
00:55:48.928 --> 00:55:51.431
But Mr. Park's wife hasn't arrived yet.

1052
00:55:53.683 --> 00:55:55.351
What if she doesn't turn up?

1053
00:55:55.435 --> 00:55:57.312
She could've just taken the money.

1054
00:55:57.395 --> 00:55:58.271
She'll come.

1055
00:55:58.354 --> 00:55:59.647
I'm sure of it.

1056
00:56:00.273 --> 00:56:02.650
She'll come for the remaining amount.

1057
00:56:02.734 --> 00:56:04.319
It's already been ten minutes.

1058
00:56:11.993 --> 00:56:13.661
It's a princess.

1059
00:56:13.745 --> 00:56:14.829
Sorry I'm late.

1060
00:56:15.413 --> 00:56:17.207
As you see. I had to put in some effort.

1061
00:56:19.918 --> 00:56:21.377
How about a brief introduction?

1062
00:56:21.461 --> 00:56:24.964
You met them at the wedding. My employees.

1063
00:56:25.048 --> 00:56:25.965
Gyeong-buk. come here.

1064
00:56:26.633 --> 00:56:28.551
This is our son. Gyeong-buk.

1065
00:56:29.469 --> 00:56:31.262
I have a son?

1066
00:56:32.806 --> 00:56:34.349
You never mentioned that.

1067
00:56:34.432 --> 00:56:36.017
I'm introducing him to you now.

1068
00:56:37.060 --> 00:56:38.645
You're so pretty.

1069
00:56:38.728 --> 00:56:40.897
Uncle. I like her.

1070
00:56:42.649 --> 00:56:44.901
Nice to meet you. I'm Gyeong-buk.

1071
00:56:47.487 --> 00:56:48.613
Nice to meet you.

1072
00:56:52.283 --> 00:56:53.201
And this…

1073
00:56:53.952 --> 00:56:56.412
I'm your father-in-law.

1074
00:56:56.996 --> 00:56:59.666
Since everyone's gathered now.
let's take the photo.

1075
00:57:00.166 --> 00:57:02.418
Bonjour. charming lady.

1076
00:57:12.095 --> 00:57:13.638
Is everyone ready?

1077
00:57:13.721 --> 00:57:14.722
-Yes.
-Yes.

1078
00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:17.851
You're a family. aren't you?

1079
00:57:18.351 --> 00:57:19.435
-Yes.
-Yes.

1080
00:57:19.519 --> 00:57:21.187
Your configuration is a bit awkward.

1081
00:57:23.314 --> 00:57:24.983
-Okay.
-I can move.

1082
00:57:25.066 --> 00:57:26.609
Let's go with option two. then.

1083
00:57:27.610 --> 00:57:29.529
I'll sit on this side.

1084
00:57:31.906 --> 00:57:35.118
If it's your first family photo.
you might feel a bit awkward.

1085
00:57:35.201 --> 00:57:38.496
You're leaving a lasting memory.
so let me help place you.

1086
00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:39.914
-The grandfather?
-Yes?

1087
00:57:39.998 --> 00:57:41.416
Please sit in the armchair.

1088
00:57:41.499 --> 00:57:42.792
-Here?
-Yes.

1089
00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:44.752
Right. I did think it was weird.

1090
00:57:44.836 --> 00:57:45.670
Move.

1091
00:57:46.713 --> 00:57:49.174
He told me to sit here.

1092
00:57:51.092 --> 00:57:53.052
And the father and mother.

1093
00:57:53.136 --> 00:57:54.220
Sit on the loveseat.

1094
00:57:54.304 --> 00:57:56.014
The father can sit in the middle.

1095
00:57:56.723 --> 00:57:58.057
Oh. I'm the mother.

1096
00:58:00.018 --> 00:58:01.060
And our little prince.

1097
00:58:01.144 --> 00:58:03.062
Why don't you sit on your dad's lap?

1098
00:58:11.696 --> 00:58:14.407
My nephew. you should sit with your dad.

1099
00:58:14.491 --> 00:58:15.992
He loves his uncle.

1100
00:58:16.493 --> 00:58:17.327
Right.

1101
00:58:17.911 --> 00:58:19.454
And the others. stand in the back.

1102
00:58:19.537 --> 00:58:21.998
All right. One. two. three.

1103
00:58:26.878 --> 00:58:28.379
One last time. everyone.

1104
00:58:28.463 --> 00:58:31.549
One. two. smile!

1105
00:58:34.219 --> 00:58:35.136
<i>I'm going to win.</i>

1106
00:58:35.220 --> 00:58:36.971
<i>I'll win no matter what.</i>

1107
00:58:37.764 --> 00:58:41.976
<i>I'll win and save Yong-man</i>
<i>and protect my guys.</i>

1108
00:58:42.060 --> 00:58:43.102
<i>I'll make sure of it.</i>

1109
00:59:23.101 --> 00:59:24.936
Dad! Mom!

1110
00:59:25.019 --> 00:59:26.479
Grandpa! Uncle!

1111
00:59:26.563 --> 00:59:28.273
Hurry up!

1112
00:59:36.531 --> 00:59:38.449
THE APARTMENT JOB

1113
01:00:02.557 --> 01:00:03.516
I'm Park Hae-kang.

1114
01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:04.601
I'm Jang Suk-jin.

1115
01:00:04.684 --> 01:00:06.394
You're quite handsome.

1116
01:00:06.477 --> 01:00:09.355
<i>Was having three candidates</i>
<i>part of your perfect plan?</i>

1117
01:00:09.439 --> 01:00:10.732
<i>What do you think. Mr. Kim?</i>

1118
01:00:10.815 --> 01:00:14.569
Do you think Park Hae-kang
can be a diligent worker for True Value?

1119
01:00:14.652 --> 01:00:17.196
<i>"I'll be a diligent worker</i>
<i>for True Value."</i>

1120
01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:18.823
<i>How exactly do you plan on doing that?</i>

1121
01:00:18.906 --> 01:00:20.908
-I'll take care of this problem!
-Win-win!

1122
01:00:20.992 --> 01:00:22.994
Deliveries will be sorted by building

1123
01:00:23.077 --> 01:00:25.455
and handed over directly
after verifying the recipient.

1124
01:00:25.538 --> 01:00:26.372
Delivery!

1125
01:00:26.456 --> 01:00:28.666
<i>Everyone can just take</i>
<i>their own packages home.</i>

1126
01:00:28.750 --> 01:00:30.251
How long will they keep this up?

1127
01:00:30.335 --> 01:00:32.670
"Request to discontinue
the delivery service"?

1128
01:00:32.754 --> 01:00:34.631
<i>The proof of delivery photos look fine.</i>

1129
01:00:34.714 --> 01:00:36.924
Boss. this is Candidate Jang's place.

1130
01:00:37.008 --> 01:00:38.676
<i>She's going negative</i>
<i>over a building rep election?</i>

1131
01:00:38.760 --> 01:00:40.511
Let's take down

1132
01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:41.721
<i>Jang Suk-jin.</i>

1133
01:00:44.891 --> 01:00:46.893
